            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Gradually whisk 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[175ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong>, the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> and your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> into the roux, and cook for 4-5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Once thickened, stir through the <strong>grated cheddar</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>torn mozzarella </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1686133786477-x200.jpg",
